What is a server?
A server is a computer or system that provides resources, data, services, or programs to other computers, known as clients, over a network.

What is the role of the domain name?
A domain name serves as a human-readable address for accessing websites and resources on the internet.

What type of DNS record is www in www.foobar.com?
The "www" in www.foobar.com is typically an A (Address) record or a CNAME (Canonical Name) record.

What is the role of the web server?
A web server delivers web pages to clients' browsers by handling HTTP requests.

What is the role of the application server?
An application server processes business logic and handles dynamic content for web applications.

What is the role of the database?
A database stores, organizes, and manages data for applications.

What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website?
The server uses the HTTP or HTTPS protocols to communicate with the user's computer.

SPOF (Single Point of Failure):
A SPOF is a component in a system that, if it fails, will stop the entire system from working.

Downtime when maintenance needed:
Downtime occurs during maintenance because services must be stopped and restarted, causing temporary unavailability.

Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic:
A system that cannot scale effectively will struggle to handle increased traffic, leading to performance issues or crashes.